'''Trefi''' in [[Welsh language|Welsh]] or '''Trevi''' in [[English language|English]] is derived from the term for a person from the [[Trevethin]] area of [[South Wales]]. It is commonly used derogatorally, as [[chav]], [[townie]] or [[pikey]], but sometimes it is simply an abbreviation denoting a native of the town.

Although the town is not very big or populous, the term is fairly well-used in the surrounding areas. It is notably used by the pupils of [[Ysgol Gyfun Gwynllyw]], who come from other areas of South Wales, but the school is sited in Trevethin.

